  "articleSummary": "This tutorial introduces JavaScript Promises as a mechanism for handling asynchronous operations, framing them around the binary outcomes of success (resolved) or failure (rejected). It covers common sources like `fetch` and `axios`, two creation methods (`Promise.resolve()` and the `Promise` constructor), and the core API (`.then()`, `.catch()`, `Promise.all`, `Promise.race`). The tone is beginner-friendly and explanatory, using a diagram and a side note about unresolved promises causing hangs. The intended audience is developers new to async JavaScript who need a clear, practical overview.",
